## Authors
Preeti Sunar, Vulluri Navya Sri, Shake Ismail, Palepu Dhana Sekhar, Amjuri Lakshmiprasad

## Abstract
A multi-role learning management system plays an important role in supporting academic activities within modern educational institutions. This system enables effective interaction among administrators, faculty members, and students using a web-based platform. The system is developed using Java, Spring Boot, and MySQL, incorporating secure authentication and role-based authorization. It improves efficiency, data consistency, and reduces manual workload.

## Key Features
- Role-Based Access Control (Admin, Faculty, Student)
- Secure authentication and authorization
- Course management and enrollment system
- Learning material sharing
- Academic progress tracking
- RESTful API-based architecture

## Technologies Used
- Java
- Spring Boot
- MySQL
- RESTful Services

## System Architecture
The system follows a layered architecture:
- Presentation Layer (UI)
- Application Layer (Business Logic)
- Data Layer (Database)

## Results
- Login response time: ~420 ms
- Course enrollment time: ~510 ms
- Role-based access accuracy: 100%
- Supports 50+ concurrent users

## Conclusion
The system improves academic management by automating processes and ensuring secure role-based interaction. It is scalable, efficient, and suitable for educational institutions.

